⛓ TATTOO TIME ⛓ Finished the final day @twohandstattoo Tattoo Time with such a breathtaking lineup of international + local artists…. Not to mention clients that were out of this world. I am so impressed with how well each and everyone of you sat, and how amped you all were to collect multiple pieces from each of these talented artists.  Thank you all for showing so much love to this practice that means everything to me.  This event filled my soul in ways I can’t fully express.  Biggest THANK YOU to @spidersinclaire for allowing me to participate and to @jasminemallinger for putting this all together so flawlessly… and to ALL the assistants who made sure we had everything we needed from supplies to food + water…. and solid encouragement. Also, to Bobby + the folks from Ponsonby Social Club for opening up their space. I truly love each and everyone of you.  From the bottom of my heart: I appreciate and adore you all. Until next year, thank you New Zealand 🇳🇿…. Im now going to cry my eyes out on my flight back home 🥹😂😭. ✨🫶🏽✨

⛓️ BOOKS OPEN ⛓️ San Francisco, it’s that time again. My booking request form is live + I will be answering requests throughout the day.  Priority given to flash, backpieces + folks who are flexible on design. Black + grey fineline trad, limited color palettes, and geometric works to the front.  I will take on a limited amount of custom works so I can attempt to have a sliver of a personal life 😅😂. Thank you all for your understanding + continued support. I could not do this with out you.  I also have space available for Austin, South Africa, Los Angeles and New York, so if you’re in those areas, please feel free to send a booking request in.  Serious inquiries only, and please make sure to check your spam folders as Gmail loves to hate me 💅🏽 Booking form link is below, in my bio, on my website + linked on all the flash pieces in my highlights and story.  New flash just posted, so please check out my highlights section for what’s available. Many more pieces will be added prior to your appointments, so many to choose from. Can’t wait to hear from you~

⛓ @sa_tattooconvention ⛓ For most of my life, I have felt like an outsider. Never truly fitting into my hometown or family + never really having a support system to rely on.  Shaky family dynamics (for better or worse) have made me walk this journey called life relatively solo.  As appreciative as I am for the strength it’s given me, there is always a part of me that has yearned for community, a sense of belonging + to be truly seen.  This photo is evidence of one of the few moments I’ve genuinely felt a part of something.  A sense of belonging….. community… being around humans who make me feel authentically seen and accepted.  These are the moments that make life worth living, and their value is immeasurable.  To the new friends I made, I know many of you will be lifelong… to those whom our friendship was strengthened, I adore you… and to the ones that have been + will continue to remain family to me: THANK YOU.  From the bottom of my heart, you’ve given me joy I don’t know I’ve truly ever felt.  I appreciate each and everyone of you + cannot wait to reconnect next year.  Biggest THANK YOU to @waldodelrocca @romanycream + Michelle for all their generosity + hard work. Events like this are not easy, especially curated in this fashion. Thank you for allowing me to be a part of it. I appreciate you all more than you know. xx~

✨THREE YEARS✨ Three years ago today, I officially opened the doors of The Helm. I spent countless nights, that turned into months renovating a storefront in dire straits.  There were times I wanted to give up, but something inside me wouldn’t let me quit. I want to thank each and everyone of you who have supported me along this journey… from the artists, guests, clients and mentors.  You have all helped facilitate a dream come true.

As a token of my appreciation, any client who books an appointment with one of our artists listed in our shop bio, from today until October 31 will receive a $100 gift card for a future appointment or merch. We look forward to many more years with y’all~
